methods.interpolate:
Interpolates input data and evaluates the interpolation at a set of desired points.

:param x: (double[]) - input x data.
:param y: (double[]) - input y data.
:param xi: (double[]) - x points to evaluate the interpolation at.
:param method: (io.deephaven.numerics.interpolation.Interpolator.InterpolationAlgorithm) - interpolation method to use.
:param extrapolate: (boolean) - true if extrapolation is to be used for values outside of the x range; false if values outside
        the x range should return NaN.
:return: (double[]) y values interpolated at points xi if xi is in range(x), and y values extrapolated based on the
         extrapolate flag if xi is not in range(x).

text: A clean interface for performing interpolations.
